column2: Two antennae met on a roof, fell madly in love and got married. The wedding ceremony wasn't very special, but the reception was excellent.
Lazy people fact #28492124. You were too lazy to read that number.
I asked my son why his password for the Disney website was MickeyGoofyPlutoDonald. He told me: 'Well, it had to have at least 4 characters.'
Two small kids talk. First kid, 'Why are there two holes in your nose?' Other kid, 'Easy, so you can still breathe when you pick your nose!'
Important update: the seminar on Time Travel has been rescheduled to the day before yesterday.
Last night I went to a 24-hour grocery. They were just locking up. I said, 'Hey, the sign says you're open 24 hours.' Clerk: 'Not in a row!'
Q: What do you call a cow on a trampoline? A: A milk shake!
Q: How do you make a tissue dance? A: You put a little boogie in it.
